01:12:05.600 --> 01:12:10.600
of how many incredible
movements have been launched

01:12:12.220 --> 01:12:14.103
since Donald Trump was elected.

01:12:15.650 --> 01:12:19.050
From the, from immigrants protections

01:12:19.050 --> 01:12:23.203
to the women's march,
to the Me, Too moment,

01:12:24.457 --> 01:12:28.926
to the successful struggle
to oppose the repeal

01:12:28.926 --> 01:12:33.090
of Obamacare, even
though Trump had control

01:12:33.090 --> 01:12:38.090
of both houses of Congress,
to the most recent efforts

01:12:38.320 --> 01:12:42.990
of high school students to
respond to mass shootings.

01:12:42.990 --> 01:12:46.460
It's really pretty remarkable, and to me,

01:12:46.460 --> 01:12:48.770
that is where our salvation lies,

01:12:48.770 --> 01:12:52.910
and so I'll close with a
quote from Learned Hand,

01:12:52.910 --> 01:12:55.790
Learned Hand was a judge
on the United States Court

01:12:55.790 --> 01:12:58.090
of Appeals for the Second Circuit,

01:12:58.090 --> 01:13:01.030
he's often said to be
greatest federal judge not

01:13:01.030 --> 01:13:03.540
to have served on the Supreme Court.

01:13:03.540 --> 01:13:05.260
Now that my wife is a federal judge,

01:13:05.260 --> 01:13:09.423
I can't agree with that, but
he was a pretty good judge,

01:13:10.809 --> 01:13:14.130
and he made a speech in 1942 to

01:13:15.090 --> 01:13:20.090
a crowd of 150,000 newly
naturalized citizens,

01:13:21.602 --> 01:13:24.450
and this was a remarkable
naturalization ceremony,

01:13:24.450 --> 01:13:27.510
it was held in Central
Park, 150,000 immigrants

01:13:27.510 --> 01:13:29.890
who had taken the oath to become citizens,

01:13:29.890 --> 01:13:34.270
and they asked Learned Hand
to address these new members

01:13:34.270 --> 01:13:38.110
of our polity, and he
decided to speak about

01:13:39.830 --> 01:13:40.663
liberty.

01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:43.580
And he said

01:13:43.580 --> 01:13:47.937
that, "Liberty lies in the hearts

01:13:47.937 --> 01:13:52.930
"of men and women, when it lies there,"

01:13:52.930 --> 01:13:53.763
or, no.

01:13:53.763 --> 01:13:58.457
"When it dies there, no
court, no constitution,

01:13:58.457 --> 01:14:03.107
"no law can save it,
but when it lies there,

01:14:03.107 --> 01:14:07.037
"it needs no court, no constitution,

01:14:07.037 --> 01:14:09.847
"no law to save it."

01:14:11.330 --> 01:14:14.200
And like many great quotes,
it's an overstatement,

01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:17.930
we need courts, we need a
constitution, we need laws,

01:14:17.930 --> 01:14:21.910
they instantiate our
ideals, and hold us to them

01:14:21.910 --> 01:14:24.760
in moments when we fall short.

01:14:24.760 --> 01:14:28.810
But it recognizes a critical truth,

01:14:28.810 --> 01:14:32.840
and that is that the ultimate protector

01:14:32.840 --> 01:14:34.370
of

01:14:34.370 --> 01:14:36.563
liberty is us,

01:14:37.750 --> 01:14:39.820
and so, to me,

01:14:39.820 --> 01:14:44.400
what is most hopeful about this moment

01:14:44.400 --> 01:14:49.400
is that us, we, have stood
up like never before,

01:14:49.800 --> 01:14:51.220
in my

01:14:51.220 --> 01:14:55.900
lifetime, as a citizen, to come together

01:14:55.900 --> 01:14:59.460
in defense of basic civil
liberties and civil rights.

01:14:59.460 --> 01:15:04.460
And so I'm, I feel privileged
to be part of that battle,

01:15:05.150 --> 01:15:08.740
but I am buoyed by the fact that so many

01:15:08.740 --> 01:15:12.450
of our fellow citizens
are part of that battle,

01:15:12.450 --> 01:15:15.930
and I hope all of you will be part of

01:15:15.930 --> 01:15:18.243
that battle going forward,
thank you very much.

01:15:18.243 --> 01:15:21.243
(audience applauds)

