in our election, is outrageous,

01:35:58.960 --> 01:36:03.280
and any president who had any,

01:36:03.280 --> 01:36:07.250
you know, legitimate
concern for the future

01:36:07.250 --> 01:36:12.250
of our democracy would respond seriously

01:36:12.420 --> 01:36:14.040
to that, to that attack.

01:36:14.040 --> 01:36:19.040
And instead, we have a
president who is unwilling

01:36:20.010 --> 01:36:21.520
to take that threat seriously,

01:36:21.520 --> 01:36:24.630
so I think it's a threat
we need to take seriously,

01:36:24.630 --> 01:36:28.190
I think it's a, you know,
that one of the dangers

01:36:28.190 --> 01:36:30.980
of social media is that it,
is that it is accessible

01:36:30.980 --> 01:36:33.220
to people far beyond our borders,

01:36:33.220 --> 01:36:36.520
who have no legitimate
voice in our democracy,

01:36:36.520 --> 01:36:40.240
and, and are exercising that voice.

01:36:40.240 --> 01:36:43.130
That problem, I think, we could solve,

01:36:43.130 --> 01:36:45.653
I think, you know, dealing with bots,

01:36:46.510 --> 01:36:50.470
identifying the sources of certain kinds

01:36:50.470 --> 01:36:53.739
of news information,

01:36:53.739 --> 01:36:56.320
and social media

01:36:56.320 --> 01:36:57.950
interventions,

01:36:57.950 --> 01:37:00.894
we could, we could
respond to that, I think.

01:37:00.894 --> 01:37:05.400
But no, I think the problem
is quite the opposite,

01:37:05.400 --> 01:37:07.560
that we're not doing enough to respond

01:37:07.560 --> 01:37:10.090
to that problem, than
that we're doing too much.

01:37:10.090 --> 01:37:12.080
- Thank you, I came in despondent,

01:37:12.080 --> 01:37:14.762
and now maybe I'm a little bit hopeful?

01:37:14.762 --> 01:37:16.420
(audience laughs)

01:37:16.420 --> 01:37:19.700
To give you more hope, we
have refreshments in the back,

01:37:19.700 --> 01:37:23.553
I hope you'll join us
in thanking David Cole.

01:37:23.553 --> 01:37:26.553
(audience applauds)

01:37:28.788 --> 01:37:31.371
